selector.name: add()
selector.description: Adds elements to the set of matched elements

selector.name: addBack()
selector.description: Adds the previous set of elements to the current set

selector.name: andSelf()
selector.description: Deprecated in version 1.8. An alias for addBack()

selector.name: children()
selector.description: Returns all direct children of the selected element

selector.name: closest()
selector.description: Returns the first ancestor of the selected element

selector.name: contents()
selector.description: Returns all direct children of the selected element (including text and comment nodes)

selector.name: each()
selector.description: Executes a function for each matched element

selector.name: end()
selector.description: Ends the most recent filtering operation in the current chain, and return the set of matched elements to its previous state

selector.name: eq()
selector.description: Returns an element with a specific index number of the selected elements

selector.name: filter()
selector.description: Reduce the set of matched elements to those that match the selector or pass the function's test

selector.name: find()
selector.description: Returns descendant elements of the selected element

selector.name: first()
selector.description: Returns the first element of the selected elements

selector.name: has()
selector.description: Returns all elements that have one or more elements inside of them

selector.name: is()
selector.description: Checks the set of matched elements against a selector/element/jQuery object, and return true if at least one of these elements matches the given arguments

selector.name: last()
selector.description: Returns the last element of the selected elements

selector.name: map()
selector.description: Passes each element in the matched set through a function, producing a new jQuery object containing the return values

selector.name: next()
selector.description: Returns the next sibling element of the selected element

selector.name: nextAll()
selector.description: Returns all next sibling elements of the selected element

selector.name: nextUntil()
selector.description: Returns all next sibling elements between two given arguments

selector.name: not()
selector.description: Returns elements that do not match a certain criteria

selector.name: offsetParent()
selector.description: Returns the first positioned parent element

selector.name: parent()
selector.description: Returns the direct parent element of the selected element

selector.name: parents()
selector.description: Returns all ancestor elements of the selected element

selector.name: parentsUntil()
selector.description: Returns all ancestor elements between two given arguments

selector.name: prev()
selector.description: Returns the previous sibling element of the selected element

selector.name: prevAll()
selector.description: Returns all previous sibling elements of the selected element

selector.name: prevUntil()
selector.description: Returns all previous sibling elements between two given arguments

selector.name: siblings()
selector.description: Returns all sibling elements of the selected element

selector.name: slice()
selector.description: Reduces the set of matched elements to a subset specified by a range of indices
